{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17596948","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17596948"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:19:39+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:19:39+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15420"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15420","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15420"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0,0,0.46,0.04,0.5]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8111"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66752"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8111","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8111"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15420"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52206"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4946"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8755"},{"type":"tags","id":"9966"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19671"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19674"},{"type":"contributions","id":"22308"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66752","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/66752"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ELiver cirrhosis represents the end stage of chronic liver injury characterised by specific histological changes.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most characteristic histological feature of nodular cirrhosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Bile duct proliferation","Fatty change","Kupffer cell hyperplasia","Portal vein thrombosis","Regenerating nodules"],"correctOptions":[4],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe defining histological features of cirrhosis include \u003Cstrong\u003Eregenerating nodules\u003C/strong\u003E of hepatocytes surrounded by fibrous septa. While \u003Cstrong\u003Efatty change\u003C/strong\u003E may be present in some cases, it is not a defining feature. \u003Cstrong\u003EBile duct proliferation\u003C/strong\u003E can occur but is not specific to cirrhosis. \u003Cstrong\u003EPortal vein thrombosis\u003C/strong\u003E is a possible complication but not a characteristic histological finding. \u003Cstrong\u003EKupffer cell hyperplasia\u003C/strong\u003E may be present but is not diagnostic.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe regenerating nodules form in response to chronic liver injury as hepatocytes attempt to restore liver function. These nodules are surrounded by fibrous bands that disrupt the normal liver architecture, leading to portal hypertension and liver dysfunction.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Nodular cirrhosis is characterised by regenerating hepatocyte nodules surrounded by fibrous septa","Chronic inflammation with mononuclear cell infiltrates is a common feature of cirrhosis"],"references":["Gawrieh S, Wilson LA, Cummings OW, Clark JM, Loomba R, Hameed B, Abdelmalek MF, Dasarathy S, Neuschwander-Tetri BA, Kowdley K, Kleiner D, Doo E, Tonascia J, Sanyal A, Chalasani N; NASH Clinical Research Network. Histologic Findings of Advanced Fibrosis and Cirrhosis in Patients With Nonalcoholic Fatty Liver Disease Who Have Normal Aminotransferase Levels. Am J Gastroenterol. 2019 Oct;114(10):1626-1635. doi: 10.14309/ajg.0000000000000388. PMID: 31517638; PMCID: PMC6800246.","Sharma B, John S. Hepatic Cirrhosis. [Updated 2022 Oct 31]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK482419/","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kurtovic E, Limaiem F. Mallory Bodies. 2024 Apr 30. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 31424884","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52206"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15420"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"52206","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/52206"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-01T21:15:13+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-01T21:15:56+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8111"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"66752"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCoun